# API

Every public symbol exported from `@nkwib/tapedeck`. Source of truth:
[`src/index.ts`](https://github.com/nkwib/tapedeck/blob/main/src/index.ts).

| Export | Kind | What it does |
|---|---|---|
| [`cassetteMiddleware`](#cassetteMiddleware) | function | Record/replay/live middleware for `wrapLanguageModel`. |
| [`withCassette`](#withCassette) | function | Vitest helper: pin a test to a named cassette. |
| [`CassetteError`](#CassetteError) | class | Base class for the whole error family. |
| [`CassetteMissError`](#CassetteMissError) | class | Replay miss â€” no cassette matched the hash. |
| [`CassetteSecretError`](#CassetteSecretError) | class | A replayed cassette still holds unredacted secrets. |
| [`CassetteCorruptError`](#CassetteCorruptError) | class | Unreadable cassette: bad JSON, version, or shape. |
| [`CassetteModeError`](#CassetteModeError) | class | Invalid mode string. |
| [`computeCassetteHash`](#computeCassetteHash) | function | The stable hash used for cassette identity. |
| [`loadCassette`](#loadCassette) | function | Read a hash-addressed cassette from a directory. |
| [`saveCassette`](#saveCassette) | function | Write a hash-addressed cassette into a directory. |
| [`stableStringify`](#stableStringify) | function | Deterministic, key-sorted JSON. |
| [`normalizeTools`](#normalizeTools) | function | Strip tool descriptions before hashing. |
| [`cassetteFilename`](#cassetteFilename) | function | On-disk filename for a hash. |
| [`CASSETTE_VERSION`](#CASSETTE_VERSION) | const | Current cassette format version. |
| [`REDACTED`](#REDACTED) | const | Placeholder written in place of a secret. |
| [`DEFAULT_REDACT`](#DEFAULT_REDACT) | const | Built-in key matchers. |

---

<ApiSignature
  id="cassetteMiddleware"
  name="cassetteMiddleware"
  kind="function"
  signature={`function cassetteMiddleware(options?: CassetteMiddlewareOptions): LanguageModelV3Middleware`}
/>

Returns an AI SDK `LanguageModelV3Middleware` for use with `wrapLanguageModel`.
Intercepts both `doGenerate` (one-shot) and `doStream` (streaming). Behaviour is
driven by `mode` â€” typically read from an env var, so you switch between recording
and replaying with no other code changes. A bad static `mode` throws
[`CassetteModeError`](#CassetteModeError) eagerly, even before the first call.

| Option | Type | Default | Description |
|--------|------|---------|-------------|
| `mode` | `'record' \| 'replay' \| 'live'` | `'live'` | Operating mode. `record` calls the real model and persists request + response; `replay` serves a cassette by hash and throws on a miss; `live` is passthrough. |
| `cassetteDir` | `string` | `'./cassettes'` | Directory cassettes are read from / written to. |
| `redact` | `(string \| RegExp)[]` | `[]` | Extra key matchers, merged with [`DEFAULT_REDACT`](#DEFAULT_REDACT). Strings match field/header names case-insensitively; RegExps test the raw key. |
| `cassetteName` | `string` | &mdash; | Force a specific filename instead of hash-addressed lookup. Mostly used internally by [`withCassette`](#withCassette); set it for fixed fixtures. |

```ts
import { openai } from '@ai-sdk/openai';
import { generateText, wrapLanguageModel } from 'ai';
import { cassetteMiddleware } from '@nkwib/tapedeck';

const model = wrapLanguageModel({
  model: openai('gpt-4o'),
  middleware: cassetteMiddleware({
    mode: process.env.CASSETTE_MODE ?? 'live', // record | replay | live
    cassetteDir: './cassettes',
    redact: ['apiKey', 'authorization', /token/i],
  }),
});

const { text } = await generateText({ model, prompt: 'Say hi' });
```

When the ambient [`withCassette`](#withCassette) context is active, its `mode`,
`cassetteDir`, and `cassetteName` take precedence over the values passed here.

<Callout kind="info" title="Streaming is first-class">
  In <code>record</code> mode tapedeck drains the live stream, persists the
  ordered parts, then re-serves them so your code still receives the response. In
  <code>replay</code> mode the parts are replayed as a genuine
  <code>ReadableStream</code> via the SDK's own
  <code>simulateReadableStream</code>.
</Callout>

<ApiSignature
  id="withCassette"
  name="withCassette"
  kind="function"
  signature={`function withCassette<T>(
  cassetteName: string,
  testFn: () => T | Promise<T>,
  options?: WithCassetteOptions
): Promise<T>`}
/>

From `@nkwib/tapedeck/vitest`. Runs `testFn` with `cassetteName` pinned and `replay`
forced for its duration, publishing an ambient context (via `AsyncLocalStorage`)
that any active [`cassetteMiddleware`](#cassetteMiddleware) instance picks up. The
context tears down automatically on exit â€” no global setup/teardown needed.

`options.mode` overrides the forced `replay`; `options.cassetteDir` overrides the
directory. The `WithCassetteOptions` shape is `&lbrace; cassetteDir?: string; mode?: CassetteMode &rbrace;`.

```ts
import { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';
import { withCassette } from '@nkwib/tapedeck/vitest';

describe('checkout agent', () => {
  it('runs the checkout flow', async () => {
    await withCassette('checkout-flow.json', async () => {
      const result = await runAgent({ prompt: 'buy a t-shirt' });
      expect(result.steps).toHaveLength(3);
    });
  });
});
```

<Callout kind="info" title="Re-exported core surface">
  <code>tapedeck/vitest</code> also re-exports
  <code>cassetteMiddleware</code> and the <code>CassetteMiddlewareOptions</code> /
  <code>CassetteMode</code> types, so a test file can import everything it needs
  from the one entry point.
</Callout>

<ApiSignature
  id="CassetteError"
  name="CassetteError"
  kind="class"
  signature={`class CassetteError extends Error {}`}
/>

The base class every tapedeck error extends. Catch it to handle the whole family
with a single `instanceof`. The constructor sets `name` from the concrete
subclass and restores the prototype chain (`Object.setPrototypeOf`), so
`instanceof` works across module boundaries and downlevel transpilation.

```ts
import { CassetteError } from '@nkwib/tapedeck';

try {
  await generateText({ model, prompt });
} catch (err) {
  if (err instanceof CassetteError) {
    // a miss, a leaked secret, a corrupt file, or a bad mode
  }
  throw err;
}
```

<ApiSignature
  id="CassetteMissError"
  name="CassetteMissError"
  kind="class"
  signature={`class CassetteMissError extends CassetteError {
  readonly hash: string;
  readonly cassetteDir: string;
  readonly cassettePath: string;
}`}
/>

Thrown in `replay` mode when no cassette matches the request hash. The message
embeds the computed hash, the path searched, and a hint to re-run with
`CASSETTE_MODE=record`. This is the load-bearing failure: a changed prompt or
tool schema produces a different hash, misses, and fails CI loudly instead of
replaying stale data.

<ApiSignature
  id="CassetteSecretError"
  name="CassetteSecretError"
  kind="class"
  signature={`class CassetteSecretError extends CassetteError {
  readonly paths: string[];
  readonly cassettePath: string | undefined;
}`}
/>

Thrown when a cassette being replayed still contains a value that the active
`redact` matchers would have stripped â€” i.e. a secret leaked into a committed
cassette. `paths` lists the offending dotted field paths so the leak is easy to
locate before it ships.

<ApiSignature
  id="CassetteCorruptError"
  name="CassetteCorruptError"
  kind="class"
  signature={`class CassetteCorruptError extends CassetteError {
  readonly cassettePath: string;
  readonly reason: string;
}`}
/>

Thrown when a cassette file exists but is unreadable: invalid JSON, an unknown or
missing version, a malformed response shape, or a response type that doesn't
match the call (a `stream` cassette served to `doGenerate`, or vice versa).

<ApiSignature
  id="CassetteModeError"
  name="CassetteModeError"
  kind="class"
  signature={`class CassetteModeError extends CassetteError {
  readonly mode: string;
}`}
/>

Thrown when an invalid mode string is supplied â€” anything other than `record`,
`replay`, or `live`. Raised eagerly at middleware construction when `mode` is
statically set, and otherwise when the ambient context resolves.

<ApiSignature
  id="computeCassetteHash"
  name="computeCassetteHash"
  kind="function"
  signature={`function computeCassetteHash(request: CassetteRequestKey): string`}
/>

The stable hash that gives a cassette its identity. Returns the bare hex SHA-256
digest of the canonicalized, key-sorted JSON of
`&lbrace; modelProvider, modelId, prompt, toolSchemas, maxOutputTokens, temperature, topP &rbrace;`.
Tool schemas are normalized first (see [`normalizeTools`](#normalizeTools)), so
cosmetic description changes don't invalidate a cassette but a changed prompt,
input schema, or sampling param does.

```ts
import { computeCassetteHash } from '@nkwib/tapedeck';

const hash = computeCassetteHash({
  modelProvider: 'openai',
  modelId: 'gpt-4o',
  prompt: [{ role: 'user', content: [{ type: 'text', text: 'Say hi' }] }],
  temperature: 0.7,
});
// '9f2câ€¦' (bare hex; callers prefix 'sha256:' for display)
```

<ApiSignature
  id="loadCassette"
  name="loadCassette"
  kind="function"
  signature={`function loadCassette(hash: string, dir: string): Promise<Cassette | null>`}
/>

Read a hash-addressed cassette from `dir`. Resolves to `null` on a miss (the file
doesn't exist) and throws [`CassetteCorruptError`](#CassetteCorruptError) for a
file that exists but is unreadable or malformed.

<ApiSignature
  id="saveCassette"
  name="saveCassette"
  kind="function"
  signature={`function saveCassette(hash: string, dir: string, cassette: Cassette): Promise<void>`}
/>

Write `cassette` into `dir` under its hash-addressed filename, creating parent
directories as needed. The file is pretty-printed JSON so it diffs cleanly in PRs.

<ApiSignature
  id="stableStringify"
  name="stableStringify"
  kind="function"
  signature={`function stableStringify(value: unknown): string`}
/>

Deterministic `JSON.stringify`: object keys are emitted in sorted order at every
level, so semantically equal requests serialize identically. The canonicalization
primitive underneath [`computeCassetteHash`](#computeCassetteHash).

<ApiSignature
  id="normalizeTools"
  name="normalizeTools"
  kind="function"
  signature={`function normalizeTools(tools: CassetteRequestKey['tools']): unknown`}
/>

Strip `description` fields recursively from a tool array before hashing.
Descriptions are irrelevant to behaviour and churn frequently, so dropping them
keeps a cassette stable across doc-only edits while still keying on the input
schema. Returns `undefined` when `tools` is absent.

<ApiSignature
  id="cassetteFilename"
  name="cassetteFilename"
  kind="function"
  signature={`function cassetteFilename(hash: string): string`}
/>

The on-disk filename for a hash-addressed cassette: `` `${hash}.cassette.json` ``.

<ApiSignature
  id="CASSETTE_VERSION"
  name="CASSETTE_VERSION"
  kind="const"
  signature={`const CASSETTE_VERSION = 'tapedeck@0.1.0';`}
/>

The cassette format version stamped into every recorded file's `version` field.
On read, a cassette whose version doesn't start with `tapedeck@` is rejected with
[`CassetteCorruptError`](#CassetteCorruptError).

<ApiSignature
  id="REDACTED"
  name="REDACTED"
  kind="const"
  signature={`const REDACTED = '[REDACTED]';`}
/>

The placeholder string written in place of a matched secret value at record time.

<ApiSignature
  id="DEFAULT_REDACT"
  name="DEFAULT_REDACT"
  kind="const"
  signature={`const DEFAULT_REDACT: (string | RegExp)[] = [
  'apiKey',
  'authorization',
  'x-api-key',
  'bearer',
  'token',
];`}
/>

The built-in key matchers, always applied even when the caller passes none. Any
`redact` option you supply is merged on top of these â€” you extend the defaults,
never replace them.
